Package Controller

Class Controller

java.lang.Object
Controller.Controller
public class Controller extends Object
Controller is the conductor of the application. It binds the View package and the Model package and does the right calls to methods and class. The controller is composed of:
  • A map.
  • A matrix with shortest paths between two stops.
  • A class that helps to compute the tour using the TSP algorithm.
  • A list of commands.
A list of states:
  • InitialState
  • MapLoadedState
  • RequestsLoadedState
  • ComputedTourState
  • TimeoutState
  • DeleteRequestState
  • AddPickupStopState
  • AddPickupPredecessorState
  • AddDeliveryStopState
  • AddDeliveryPredecessorState
GUI components:
  • A landing page.
  • A menu.
Author:
H4122

ListOfCommands, State, Map, Path, TSP, LandingPage, Menu

    • computeOptimisedTour

      public int computeOptimisedTour​(Map tourMap)
      Computes a tour. Using the map and the Stops to visit, the shortest paths between all the allowed stops are computed with Dijkstra. A complete graph is generated using the costs calculated previously. This graph is used to create tsp and search a solution with a time limit fixed to 20 seconds. This method returns if the computation of the tsp solution managed to compute an optimal tour during the time limit or not.
      Parameters:
      tourMap - The current map
      See Also:
      computeStopPaths(ArrayList, ArrayList), generateCompleteGraph(ArrayList, Path[][]), TSP1, TemplateTSP.searchSolution(int, Model.Graph)

    • resumeComputing

      public int resumeComputing()

      See Also:

    • saveTSPSolution

      public void saveTSPSolution​(TSP tsp, Path[][] paths)
      Saves the solution of the hamiltonian path calculated with TSP either the computation is finished or not, the current solution is interpreted the nextPath attributes of each stop are updated the orderedTravel attribute is updated with the ordered stops to visit the arrival times to each stop are therefore calculated
      Parameters:
      tsp - The tsp used since the beginning of the tour computation
      paths - a matrix of all the paths between the stops of the tour
      See Also:
      TSP.getSolution(int), Map, Tour.computeArrivalTimes()
